        public void readUrl(java.lang.String inputUrl)
        Creates a HTTP GET call to the given url and calls onResult() with the result when a results arrives.

        Please note that this will be percentage encoded (rfc3986) inside this method so dont do convertions like space to %20% when calling this (eg. "%20" would end up as "%2520" which is probably not what you want)

        Parameters:
        inputUrl - The complete url to use.

      • readUrlSync

        public java.lang.String readUrlSync(java.lang.String inputUrl)
        Creates a HTTP GET call to the given url and returns the result when it arrives from the server. Use the getStatus() to check if any errors occured in the process.

        Please note that this will be percentage encoded (rfc3986) inside this method so dont do convertions like space to %20% when calling this (eg. "%20" would end up as "%2520" which is probably not what you want)

        Parameters:
        inputUrl - The complete url to use.
        Returns:
        String The content feedback recieved from the server.
